Anyway, I do think that we are
on the cusp of really being

00:48:00.200 --> 00:48:02.700
able to make a new one--

00:48:02.700 --> 00:48:05.670
things like Zipcar,
RelayRides.

00:48:05.670 --> 00:48:09.660
There's just so much we can
do with technology to do a

00:48:09.660 --> 00:48:12.460
great-- actually, just even
showing this, with car

00:48:12.460 --> 00:48:14.830
sharing, we can have
it be all around.

00:48:14.830 --> 00:48:16.230
Just go get your
neighbor's car.

00:48:16.230 --> 00:48:19.010
There's just so many
things we can do.

00:48:19.010 --> 00:48:21.710
So I just wanted to
end it there.

00:48:21.710 --> 00:48:26.730
I know it was a lot of
information very fast, but

00:48:26.730 --> 00:48:28.890
it's really--

00:48:28.890 --> 00:48:33.850
I think if we can get some of
your folks who are already

00:48:33.850 --> 00:48:37.700
with Google Transit, having
its own disruptive and

00:48:37.700 --> 00:48:41.650
wonderful influence on folks
there, can be a very big

00:48:41.650 --> 00:48:45.480
impact on how we grow.

00:48:45.480 --> 00:48:47.770
Yeah.

00:48:47.770 --> 00:48:51.710
So why don't we open it
up for questions.

00:48:51.710 --> 00:48:55.170
AUDIENCE: So the project
of the fast train to

00:48:55.170 --> 00:48:56.560
LA is really awesome.

00:48:56.560 --> 00:49:00.110
And my friend was to China and
their trains cover Beijing to

00:49:00.110 --> 00:49:02.080
Shanghai in, like,
three hours.

00:49:02.080 --> 00:49:04.990
But why does it take like
20, whatever years you

00:49:04.990 --> 00:49:06.090
said, to build it?

00:49:06.090 --> 00:49:09.610
Why China could build one
in five, right, or--

00:49:09.610 --> 00:49:11.730
so what's different?

00:49:11.730 --> 00:49:13.005
AUDIENCE: A lot of
complex reasons.

00:49:13.005 --> 00:49:16.550
STUART COHEN: A lot of
complex reasons.

00:49:16.550 --> 00:49:18.130
First off, there's definitely
the money.

00:49:18.130 --> 00:49:20.750
High-speed rail is going to cost
$68 billion here with the

00:49:20.750 --> 00:49:22.400
current plan.

00:49:22.400 --> 00:49:25.440
And we don't have the money
in our broke state.

00:49:25.440 --> 00:49:26.430
So the money is one.

00:49:26.430 --> 00:49:29.380
And then environmental review
and getting it through

00:49:29.380 --> 00:49:32.690
communities and doing the
planning right is the other.

00:49:32.690 --> 00:49:36.260
If we put our mind to it, we can
do it in faster than that.

00:49:36.260 --> 00:49:39.550
And actually, if we wanted to
take carbon fees and put it

00:49:39.550 --> 00:49:41.440
towards high-speed rail, it
could be done faster.

00:49:41.440 --> 00:49:44.700
But I wouldn't want it done less
than 10, because we want

00:49:44.700 --> 00:49:46.340
to get the planning right and
really engage communities.

00:49:46.340 --> 00:49:47.806
Real quickly.

00:49:47.806 --> 00:49:49.960
AUDIENCE: This is sort of
a specific question.

